post_cb({"bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_28135075_28135194_0": {"length": 11, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 7047}, "so_28135075_28135194_2": {"length": 23, "quality": 0.9583333333333334, "section_id": 7047}}, "n3337": {"so_28135075_28135194_0": {"length": 11, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 6792}, "so_28135075_28135194_2": {"length": 23, "quality": 0.9583333333333334, "section_id": 6792}}, "n4659": {"so_28135075_28135194_0": {"length": 11, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 8544}, "so_28135075_28135194_2": {"length": 23, "quality": 0.9583333333333334, "section_id": 8544}}}, "28135075": {"ViewCount": "814", "Body": "<pre><code>#include &lt;iostream&gt;\nusing namespace std;\n\nclass time\n{\n    private:\n        int hour;\n        int min;\n        int sec;\n    public:\n        void get_time(int h,int m,int s)\n        {\n            hour = h;\n            min = m;\n            sec = s;\n        }\n        void show_time()\n        {\n            cout &lt;&lt; \"The time is: \" &lt;&lt; hour &lt;&lt; \"hours \" &lt;&lt; min &lt;&lt; \"minutes \" &lt;&lt; sec &lt;&lt; \"seconds\";\n        }\n};\n\nint main()\n{\n    time t1;\n    t1.get_time(5, 4, 2);\n    t1.show_time();\n    return 0;\n}\n</code></pre>\n<hr>\n<pre><code>output:\n    time.cpp: In function \u2018int main()\u2019:\n    time.cpp:25:7: error: expected \u2018;\u2019 before \u2018t1\u2019\n      time t1;\n           ^\n    time.cpp:28:2: error: \u2018t1\u2019 was not declared in this scope\n      t1.get_time(5, 4, 2);\n      ^\n</code></pre>\n</hr>", "AcceptedAnswerId": "28135099", "Title": "error: expected ';' before defining object of class", "CreationDate": "2015-01-25T09:45:27.007", "Id": "28135075", "CommentCount": "1", "LastEditDate": "2015-01-25T09:48:41.310", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastEditorUserId": "3250829", "LastActivityDate": "2017-05-26T02:24:18.700", "Score": "2", "OwnerUserId": "4491609", "Tags": "<c++>", "AnswerCount": "2"}, "28135099": {"Id": "28135099", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>My compiler gives some very useful diagnostics that explain exactly what's going on:</p>\n<pre><code>$ g++ test.cpp\ntest.cpp:25:6: error: must use 'class' tag to refer to type 'time' in this scope\n            time t1;\n            ^\n            class \n/usr/include/time.h:118:8: note: class 'time' is hidden by a non-type\n      declaration of 'time' here\ntime_t time(time_t *);\n       ^\n1 error generated.\n</code></pre>\n<p>I think the best strategy is to give your class a different name (perhaps <code>Time</code> with an uppercase <code>T</code>?)</p>\n", "LastActivityDate": "2015-01-25T09:48:31.447", "Score": "1", "CreationDate": "2015-01-25T09:48:31.447", "ParentId": "28135075", "CommentCount": "0", "OwnerUserId": "367273"}, "28135194": {"Id": "28135194", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>There is a global function called <a href=\"http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/chrono/c/time\" rel=\"nofollow\"><code>time</code></a>, inherited from the C standard library. It hides your classes name, [basic.scope.declarative]/4:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_28135075_28135194_0\">Given a set of declarations in a single declarative region, each of\n  which specifies the same unqualified name,</p>\n<ul>\n<li><p id=\"so_28135075_28135194_1\">[..] </p></li>\n<li><p id=\"so_28135075_28135194_2\">exactly one declaration shall declare a class name or enumeration name that is not a typedef name\n     and the other declarations shall [..] all refer to functions\n    and function templates; <strong>in this case the class name or enumeration name is hidden (3.3.10).</strong> [..]</p></li>\n</ul>\n</blockquote>\n<p>The easiest solution is to give your class another name (e.g. <code>Time</code> - C and C++ standard libraries never use uppercase letters in identifiers).</p>\n", "LastActivityDate": "2015-01-25T10:01:57.067", "Score": "2", "CreationDate": "2015-01-25T10:01:57.067", "ParentId": "28135075", "CommentCount": "0", "OwnerUserId": "3647361"}});